rails generate controller home index   => creates a controller /home/index (in app/views/home/index.html.erb)

routes is in config


rails g resource question email:string body:text =>   sets up a table with those parameters
to make the table after that do => rake db:migrate

rails console (to use sql lite. like using mongo shell)
Question.create email: "misankovich@gmail.com", body: "how old is the universe?"

helpers are reusable methods for views. They can be built in or custom.

rake routes => displays all available routes
